FT  08 AUG 92 / The Barcelona Olympics: Russian wins 50km walk
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Russian Andrei Perlov conquered heat, humidity and the steep climb to the
Olympic stadium to take the men's 50km road walk gold medal. Perlov, second
in last year's world championships, took an early lead and held on to win in
an unofficial time of 3 hours 50.13 seconds.
Italian Carlos Mercenario was second (3:52.09) and Germany's Ronald Weigel,
1988 Olympic silver medallist, took bronze (3:53.45).
