<HEADLINE>
FT  08 AUG 92 / Finance &amp; The Family (Briefcase, Q&amp;A): No opt-out for
self-employed
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
I AM self-employed. Can I opt out of the state pension scheme, and if so,
can I get back the money and interest I have paid in?
The answer to both questions is no. Contracting-out rebates are only
available for employees taxed under Schedule E as the self-employed do not
qualify for SERPS. Contracting-out cannot be backdated.
No legal responsibility can be accepted by the Financial Times for the
answers given in these columns. All inquiries will be answered by post as
soon as possible.
