FT  08 AUG 92 / Letter: More bad news on the way?
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   From Mr GORDON HAZZARD
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Sir, Doubtless the gloomy words of Sir John Quinton, chairman of Barclays
Bank ('Recession to last 'two more years'', August 7), are encircling the
world and there must be a danger that a few people will regard his comments
as having some relevance to the economic circumstances and prospects of the
UK.
Should we not ask how it can be that a person gifted with such remarkable
economic foresight presides over a bank that incurred a billion pounds in
bad debts in one year? Should we not also conclude that Sir John's purpose
is to prepare his shareholders for more and more bad news?
Gordon Hazzard,
5 Balfour Place,
Mayfair, London W1Y 5RG
