FT  07 AUG 92 / UK Company News: Dollars 15m deal expands access side
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ANDREW BAXTER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
SIMON Engineering, the world's largest access equipment company, is paying
up to Dollars 15m (Pounds 7.8m) for Hi-Ranger line of truck-mounted
hydraulic platforms from Utility Equipment Corporation, the private US
group.
The deal continues the process of consolidation in the Pounds 1.2bn world
access equipment industry, in which Simon has played a key part with a
string of acquisitions during the past 15 years.
The consideration involves an initial Dollars 2.5m cash payment, an
additional Dollars 2.5m over the next five years, and further sales-related
payments up to a maximum of Dollars 10m.
The complex deal has taken three years to negotiate, and excludes
Hi-Ranger's US manufacturing plant. Its production of about 600 machines a
year, for turnover of Dollars 20m, will be switched to existing Simon plants
in the US.
