<TEXT>
THE proportion of 16-year-olds remaining in full-time education rose from
51.7 per cent in 1989 to 59.8 per cent last year, according to the
Department of Education. The rate for 17-year-olds rose from 35.4 per cent
to 43 per cent.
The combined figures for full-time and part-time students rose from 68.3 per
cent of 16-year-olds in 1989 to 73.2 per cent last year, and from 53.1 per
cent of 17-year-olds in 1989 to 58.8 per cent last year.
