FT  07 AUG 92 / Accountancy disciplinary move
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
ACCOUNTANCY firms should be subject to disciplinary proceedings, which may
lead to reprimands and fines, the Institute of Chartered Accountants
proposed yesterday.
A consultation paper on the relationship between the institute and the firms
calls for an extension of the institute's powers to difficulties that have
arisen through corporate decisions.
